  "root_text": {
    "sn38.16:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 38.16 ",
    "sn38.16:0.2": "1. Jambukhādakavagga ",
    "sn38.16:0.3": "Dukkarapañhāsutta ",
    "sn38.16:1.1": "“Kiṁ nu kho, āvuso sāriputta, imasmiṁ dhammavinaye dukkaran”ti? ",
    "sn38.16:1.2": "“Pabbajjā kho, āvuso, imasmiṁ dhammavinaye dukkarā”ti. ",
    "sn38.16:1.3": "“Pabbajitena panāvuso, kiṁ dukkaran”ti? ",
    "sn38.16:1.4": "“Pabbajitena kho, āvuso, abhirati dukkarā”ti. ",
    "sn38.16:1.5": "“Abhiratena panāvuso, kiṁ dukkaran”ti? ",
    "sn38.16:1.6": "“Abhiratena kho, āvuso, dhammānudhammappaṭipatti dukkarā”ti. ",
    "sn38.16:1.7": "“Kīvaciraṁ panāvuso, dhammānudhammappaṭipanno bhikkhu arahaṁ assā”ti? ",
    "sn38.16:1.8": "“Naciraṁ, āvuso”ti. ",
    "sn38.16:1.9": "Soḷasamaṁ. ",
    "sn38.16:1.10": "Jambukhādakasaṁyuttaṁ samattaṁ. ",
    "sn38.16:2.0": "Tassuddānaṁ ",
    "sn38.16:2.1": "Nibbānaṁ arahattañca, ",
    "sn38.16:2.2": "dhammavādī kimatthiyaṁ; ",
    "sn38.16:2.3": "Assāso paramassāso, ",
    "sn38.16:2.4": "vedanā āsavāvijjā; ",
    "sn38.16:2.5": "Taṇhā oghā upādānaṁ, ",
    "sn38.16:2.6": "bhavo dukkhañca sakkāyo. ",
    "sn38.16:2.7": "Imasmiṁ dhammavinaye dukkaranti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn38.16:0.1": "Linked Discourses 38.16 ",
    "sn38.16:0.2": "1. With Jambukhādaka ",
    "sn38.16:0.3": "A Question About What’s Hard to Do ",
    "sn38.16:1.1": "“Reverend Sāriputta, in this teaching and training, what is hard to do?” ",
    "sn38.16:1.2": "“Going forth, reverend, is hard to do in this teaching and training.” ",
    "sn38.16:1.3": "“But what’s hard to do for someone who has gone forth?” ",
    "sn38.16:1.4": "“When you’ve gone forth it’s hard to be satisfied.” ",
    "sn38.16:1.5": "“But what’s hard to do for someone who is satisfied?” ",
    "sn38.16:1.6": "“When you’re satisfied, it’s hard to practice in line with the teaching.” ",
    "sn38.16:1.7": "“But if a mendicant practices in line with the teaching, will it take them long to become a perfected one?” ",
    "sn38.16:1.8": "“Not long, reverend.” ",
    "sn38.16:1.9": "",
    "sn38.16:1.10": "The Linked Discourses with Jambukhādaka are complete. ",
